---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
	title="About"
	description="Build Week NYC is the builder-first alternative to sponsor-maze tech weeks. Community-driven, platform-agnostic, and designed for real discovery."
	currentPath="/about"
>
	<section style="padding-top:var(--space-2xl);">
		<div class="container">
			<div style="max-width:720px;">
				<div style="margin-bottom:var(--space-4xl);">
					<div class="hero-badge" style="margin-bottom:var(--space-lg);">
						Built by builders, for builders
					</div>

					<h1 class="display-sm" style="margin-bottom:var(--space-lg);">
						What is <em style="font-style:normal;background:var(--gradient-cta);-webkit-background-clip:text;-webkit-text-fill-color:transparent;background-clip:text;">Build Week NYC</em>?
					</h1>

					<p class="body-lg" style="color:var(--on-surface-variant);line-height:var(--leading-relaxed);margin-bottom:var(--space-lg);">
						Build Week NYC is a community-powered directory of tech events happening across New York City during the first week of June 2026. We make it effortless to find, filter, and save events whether you are into civic tech, AI agents, fintech, healthtech, or just the right room at the right time.
					</p>

					<p class="body-lg" style="color:var(--on-surface-variant);line-height:var(--leading-relaxed);">
						Unlike sponsor-first tech weeks, Build Week is deliberately community-first. Every event gets a real shot at discovery. Every RSVP platform can plug in. Every builder belongs.
					</p>
				</div>

				<div style="background:var(--surface-container-low);border-radius:var(--radius-xl);padding:var(--space-2xl);margin-bottom:var(--space-3xl);">
					<h2 class="headline-md" style="margin-bottom:var(--space-xl);">How we are different</h2>

					<div style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:var(--space-xl);">
						<div style="display:flex;gap:var(--space-md);align-items:flex-start;">
							<div style="width:40px;height:40px;border-radius:var(--radius-lg);background:var(--primary-container);display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;flex-shrink:0;">1</div>
							<div>
								<h3 class="title-md" style="margin-bottom:var(--space-2xs);">Real discovery, not click mazes</h3>
								<p class="body-md text-muted">Events are visible on the homepage. Filters stay present. The directory is the product, not a buried secondary flow.</p>
							</div>
						</div>

						<div style="display:flex;gap:var(--space-md);align-items:flex-start;">
							<div style="width:40px;height:40px;border-radius:var(--radius-lg);background:var(--secondary-container);display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;flex-shrink:0;">2</div>
							<div>
								<h3 class="title-md" style="margin-bottom:var(--space-2xs);">Platform-agnostic hosting</h3>
								<p class="body-md text-muted">Bring a Luma, Partiful, Eventbrite, or manual RSVP link. We are not forcing organizers onto a single stack.</p>
							</div>
						</div>

						<div style="display:flex;gap:var(--space-md);align-items:flex-start;">
							<div style="width:40px;height:40px;border-radius:var(--radius-lg);background:var(--tertiary-fixed);display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;flex-shrink:0;">3</div>
							<div>
								<h3 class="title-md" style="margin-bottom:var(--space-2xs);">Personal schedule that actually helps</h3>
								<p class="body-md text-muted">Save events, detect conflicts, and export your agenda to calendar without creating an account wall first.</p>
							</div>
						</div>

						<div style="display:flex;gap:var(--space-md);align-items:flex-start;">
							<div style="width:40px;height:40px;border-radius:var(--radius-lg);background:var(--surface-container-highest);display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;flex-shrink:0;">4</div>
							<div>
								<h3 class="title-md" style="margin-bottom:var(--space-2xs);">Narrative curation, not a flat dump</h3>
								<p class="body-md text-muted">Tracks give the week a point of view so attendees can move with context instead of opening twenty tabs.</p>
							</div>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>

				<div style="background:var(--surface-container);border-radius:var(--radius-xl);padding:var(--space-2xl);margin-bottom:var(--space-3xl);position:relative;overflow:hidden;">
					<div style="display:flex;gap:var(--space-2xl);align-items:flex-start;">
						<div style="flex:1;">
							<h2 class="headline-md" style="margin-bottom:var(--space-md);">Built by Chai With Jai</h2>
							<p class="body-lg" style="color:var(--on-surface-variant);line-height:var(--leading-relaxed);margin-bottom:var(--space-md);">
								Build Week NYC is a project by <strong>Jai Bhagat</strong> and the <strong>Chai With Jai</strong> community. The core bet is simple: tech weeks should help builders find the right rooms, not just amplify whoever bought the biggest logo placement.
							</p>
							<p class="body-lg" style="color:var(--on-surface-variant);line-height:var(--leading-relaxed);">
								Whether you are an immigrant founder navigating an O-1, a civic hacker building public tools, or a South Asian operator looking for your people, this week is designed to make discovery feel intentional.
							</p>
							<div style="margin-top:var(--space-xl);display:flex;gap:var(--space-sm);flex-wrap:wrap;">
								<a href="/events" class="btn btn-primary btn-sm">Browse events</a>
								<a href="/events/submit" class="btn btn-ghost btn-sm">Submit your event</a>
							</div>
						</div>
						<div class="character-inline character--hide-mobile" style="width:160px;flex-shrink:0;" aria-hidden="true">
							<img src="/characters/jai/waving.png" alt="" width="160" height="160" loading="lazy" />
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>

				<div style="text-align:center;padding:var(--space-3xl) 0;">
					<h2 class="headline-md" style="margin-bottom:var(--space-md);">Hosting during Build Week?</h2>
					<p class="body-lg text-muted" style="margin-bottom:var(--space-xl);max-width:45ch;margin-inline:auto;">
						Submit your event for review and plug into the builder-first directory.
					</p>
					<a href="/events/submit" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg">Submit your event</a>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>
</BaseLayout>
